        <heading>1007.  Testimony or written admission of party</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1007.  Testimony or written admission of party
Contents of writings, recordings, or photographs may be proved by the testimony or, in a civil case, deposition of the party against whom offered or by his written admission, without accounting for the nonproduction of the original.</p>
        </content>
